title: Raphael Warnock
added: Warnock is an advocate of policies to address climate change. He has stated that he supports the United States re-entering the [[Paris Agreement]], strengthening the [[Environmental Protection Agency]], and investing more into clean energy and green infrastructure.<ref>https://warnockforgeorgia.com/issues/climate/</ref>

title: Raphael Warnock
added: Though he has not endorsed the [[Green New Deal]], his 2020 Senate campaign was endorsed by the [[Sunrise Movement]], an organization that has called for sweeping changes to policy to fight against climate change.

title: Raphael Warnock
added: Senator-elect Warnock has pledged to vote in favor of the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. He has also been outspoken in working towards making Election Day a federal holiday and expanding early and absentee voting.<ref>https://warnockforgeorgia.com/issues/voting-rights/</ref>

title: Raphael Warnock
added: In December 2020 during his Senate campaign, a group of 25 Black ministers wrote an open letter to Warnock asking him to reconsider his stance on abortion, noting his position was "contrary to Christian teachings" and that abortion disproportionately affected the African American population.<ref>[https://www.savannahnow.com/story/news/2020/12/14/raphael-warnock-abortion-stance-criticized-black-pastors/6529810002/]</ref>
